9fcd330d-dc01-45c6-b1cc-685f4dd87f1c.text:
Let $\struct {G, \circ, \preceq}$ be an ordered group with identity $e$.
Let $\prec$ be the reflexive reduction of $\preceq$.
Let $x, y \in G$.
Then the following equivalences hold:
{{begin-axiom}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname {OG} 2.1
        | m = x \preceq y \iff e \preceq y \circ x^{-1}
}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname {OG} 2.2
        | m = x \preceq y \iff e \preceq x^{-1} \circ y
}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname {OG} 2.3
        | m = x \preceq y \iff x \circ y^{-1} \preceq e
}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname  {OG} 2.4
        | m = x \preceq y \iff y^{-1} \circ x \preceq e
}}
{{end-axiom}}
{{begin-axiom}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname {OG} 2.1'
        | m = x \prec y \iff e \prec y \circ x^{-1}
}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname {OG} 2.2'
        | m = x \prec y \iff e \prec x^{-1} \circ y
}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname {OG} 2.3'
        | m = x \prec y \iff x \circ y^{-1} \prec e
}}
{{axiom | n = \operatorname {OG} 2.4'
        | m = x \prec y \iff y^{-1} \circ x \prec e
}}
{{end-axiom}}

