{{EuclidPropStatement|book=V|prop=1|body=If there be any number of magnitudes whatever which are, respectively, equimultiples of any magnitudes equal in multitude, then, whatever multiple of one of the magnitudes is of one, that multiple also will all be of all.}}
That is, if $ma, mb, mc$ etc. be any equimultiples of $a, b, c$ etc., then:
:$m a + m b + m c + \cdots = m \paren {a + b + c + \cdots }$

